The paper deals with compression algorithms and their analysis, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The analysis involves lower bounds on the size of the grammar produced by the compression algorithms, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also proposes a new algorithm for the compression, which involves probabilistic analysis and space-time tradeoffs, which falls under the category of stochastic systems (cs.SI).
